{"total_count": 17, "incomplete_results": false, "items": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/42", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/42/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/42/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/42/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/42", "id": 608886765, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU2MDg4ODY3NjU=", "number": 42, "title": "ImportError: cannot import name 'Badge' from 'anybadge'", "user": {"login": "kagarlickij", "id": 16048228, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MDQ4MjI4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/16048228?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij", "html_url": "https://github.com/kagarlickij", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kagarlickij/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2020-04-29T08:52:26Z", "updated_at": "2020-05-25T13:17:24Z", "closed_at": "2020-05-25T13:17:24Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi there, I'm trying to use code snippet from README.md:\r\n```\r\nimport anybadge\r\n\r\n# Define thresholds: <2=red, <4=orange <8=yellow <10=green\r\nthresholds = {2: 'red',\r\n              4: 'orange',\r\n              6: 'yellow',\r\n              10: 'green'}\r\n\r\nbadge = anybadge.Badge('pylint', 2.22, thresholds=thresholds)\r\n\r\nbadge.write_badge('pylint.svg')\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd getting `ImportError: cannot import name 'Badge' from 'anybadge' ` error.\r\n\r\nReproduced in both Python 2.7 and 3.7 environments, I used Docker:\r\n```\r\nFROM python:3.7\r\nRUN apt-get update -y && \\\r\n    apt-get install nano -y && \\\r\n    pip install anybadge && \\\r\n    pip list\r\nCOPY . /opt\r\nRUN python /opt/anybadge.py\r\n```\r\n\r\n..and `anybadge.py` with code above\r\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/33", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/33/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/33/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/33/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/33", "id": 523931831, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1MjM5MzE4MzE=", "number": 33, "title": "Setup failing with errors in README.md", "user": {"login": "jongracecox", "id": 30441316, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwNDQxMzE2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/30441316?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jongracecox/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2019-11-17T04:01:52Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-17T04:19:39Z", "closed_at": "2019-11-17T04:19:39Z", "author_association": "OWNER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "While running `setup.py` I get the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"setup.py\", line 18, in <module>\r\n    ', '.join([e.message for e in errors]))\r\nValueError: ('README.md contains errors: ', 'Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Bullet list ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent., Error parsing content block for the \"list-table\" directive: two-level bullet list expected, but row 2 does not contain a second-level bullet list.')\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe command I am using is:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython3 setup.py bdist_wheel\r\n```", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/30", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/30/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/30/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/30/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/30", "id": 478318081, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NzgzMTgwODE=", "number": 30, "title": "Add documentation for using custom color codes", "user": {"login": "Sieboldianus", "id": 13646666, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ2NjY2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/13646666?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus", "html_url": "https://github.com/Sieboldianus", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sieboldianus/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2019-08-08T08:15:24Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-09T14:48:30Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-09T14:48:30Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I love anybadge and use it regularly to create any kind of badges for my projects in gitlab ci (primarily because it is small, and dependencies are installed quickly).\r\n\r\nToday I wanted to create a badge with color \"blue\" - but blue doesn't exist in the default list of colors.\r\n\r\nI've used a detour to add \"blue\" to anybadge, e.g.:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython -c \"import anybadge; anybadge.COLORS['blue'] = '#1182C3'; print(anybadge.COLORS.get('blue'))\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, this seems rather cumbersome and it is also not documented.\r\n\r\nIs there an alternative to using custom color codes I perhaps missed?", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/27", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/27/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/27/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/27/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/27", "id": 467758969, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0Njc3NTg5Njk=", "number": 27, "title": "ValueError: invalid literal for int() with base 10: '10.00'", "user": {"login": "llazzaro", "id": 568181, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU2ODE4MQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/568181?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro", "html_url": "https://github.com/llazzaro", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/llazzaro/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 7, "created_at": "2019-07-13T19:37:28Z", "updated_at": "2019-07-17T01:35:11Z", "closed_at": "2019-07-16T21:53:11Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Today our CI broke with the latest version in pipy.\r\nI saw some fix commits on the repo, not sure if it was published into pipy.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/builds/faradaysec/faraday/faraday_venv/bin/anybadge\", line 10, in <module>\r\n    sys.exit(main())\r\n  File \"/builds/faradaysec/faraday/faraday_venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/anybadge.py\", line 755, in main\r\n    value_format=args.value_format, text_color=args.text_color)\r\n  File \"/builds/faradaysec/faraday/faraday_venv/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/anybadge.py\", line 191, in __init__\r\n    value_text = str(self.value_type(value))\r\nValueError: invalid literal for int() with base 10: '10.00'\r\n```", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/25", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/25/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/25/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/25/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/25", "id": 466128896, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NjYxMjg4OTY=", "number": 25, "title": "Integer printed as float", "user": {"login": "ahogen", "id": 6827790, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY4Mjc3OTA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/6827790?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen", "html_url": "https://github.com/ahogen", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ahogen/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-07-10T06:42:12Z", "updated_at": "2019-07-12T04:59:09Z", "closed_at": "2019-07-12T01:43:49Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "While looking at [`fixed-widths`](https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/tree/fix-widths) branch for #24, I noticed that integer values seemed to get marked as `float` instead of `int` as intended. Since it's a simple fix, I didn't think it needed a full PR, but I can make one if you'd like.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/anybadge.py b/anybadge.py\r\nindex 5cc9f04..5dd00b3 100755\r\n--- a/anybadge.py\r\n+++ b/anybadge.py\r\n@@ -307,12 +307,11 @@ class Badge(object):\r\n\r\n         Returns: type\r\n         \"\"\"\r\n+        if self.value_is_int:\r\n+            return int\r\n         if self.value_is_float:\r\n             return float\r\n-        elif self.value_is_int:\r\n-            return int\r\n-        else:\r\n-            return str\r\n+        return str\r\n\r\n     @property\r\n     def label_width(self):\r\n```\r\n\r\nTest:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython ./anybadge.py -l \"test\" -v \"1234\" -f ./test.svg -o\r\n```\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n![before](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6827790/60947026-7901ad00-a2a4-11e9-84d1-ea7051ce26ea.PNG)\r\n\r\nAfter fix:\r\n![after](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6827790/60947029-7acb7080-a2a4-11e9-9463-fdbbfa2da537.PNG)\r\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/21", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/21/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/21/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/21/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/jongracecox/anybadge/issues/21", "id": 458782951, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NTg3ODI5NTE=", "number": 21, "title": "Gitlab CI: No such file or directory", "user": {"login": "mkapra", "id": 34742358, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM0NzQyMzU4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/34742358?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra", "html_url": "https://github.com/mkapra", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mkapra/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "ht